The paper deals with type theory and category theory, which are topics commonly found in the Logic (LO) and Programming Languages (PL) sub-categories. The use of Martin-Löf type theory and the focus on extensional identity suggests a connection to the Logic sub-category. The mention of locally cartesian closed categories and the use of categorical language suggest a connection to the Category Theory (CC) sub-category. Finally, the mention of undecidability and the reduction to combinatory logic suggest a connection to the Information Theory (IT) sub-category.
